column1: Old Reference OS-55090 OSF | Wave 8.2.1 | ACC1 | Incomplete OGW logs generated- Logs of Multiple services is not visible in OGW
column41:
We have observed that Multiple services logs are not getting generated in ogw.
We have created below table to track which services are visible and which services are not visible in ogw logs.
We have checked this issue for frequent used services, please find below observation.
|SOAP Action|Flow Name|Server Name|ACC2|ACC1|
|CreateFNPOrderStatus|New Activation FN|WF|Yes|No(Only response is visible)|
|SetFNOrderStatus|New Activation FN|WS|Yes|No|
|SetOrderStatus|New Activation All stacks|WS/WF|Yes|Yes|
|Fast Search|New Activation All stacks|WF|Yes|No|
|Save Document|New Activation All stacks|WF|No|No|
|GetProductAvailability|New Activation FN|WS|Yes|Yes|
|SendDocument|New Activation All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|
|GetIdentMethods|New Activation All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|
|SetPermission|Activation and ILS for All stacks|WS/WF|Yes|Yes|
|SubmitOrder|Activation and ILS for All stacks|WS/WF|Yes|Yes|
|GetOrder|Mobile New Activation (Retail)|WS|Yes|Yes|
|GetOrderList|Mobile New Activation (Retail)|WS|Yes|Yes|
|GetOrder4Archiving|Retail New Activation All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|
|GetDocuments|Retail New Activation All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|
|VFDECustomerSearch|Customer search for All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|
|OnOrderStatusChange |New Activation FN|WS|Yes|Yes|
|Tivano Input and Output|New Activation FN|WS|Yes|No|
|/MFTariffSoc-002/GetTariffSOCFeature|Mobile Customer Search|WS|Yes|Yes|
|/CustomerAccount-002/SearchCustomerBANSubscriber|Mobile Customer Search|WS|Yes|Yes|
|/BankAccountUtility-001/ValidateAndConvert|New Activation All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|
|/MFMultipleSocs-001/MaintainSoc|Mobile Change Tariff|WF|Yes|yes|
|/HardwareOrder-001/GetAvailableShippingOptions|New Activation All stacks|WS|Yes|Yes|

 

 

Steps to reproduce: 
 # Login to omnius in telesales/retail channel in ACC1
 # place any order
 # submit the order
 # observe the issue in ogw

 

Expected result: All services logs should get printed in OGW

Actual result: Mulitple services logs is not getting printed in OGW.

column1: NEW CR OSF | ACC1 | Wave 8.2 | sliding prices are not interpreted as expected
column41:
{color:#ff0000}The priority is set to "Blocker" as the issue is a show stopper for the Go Live of : [https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PORPDT-79] 
Without a fix the feature can not be deployed into production.{color}

 

Test data:

Browser: Chrome
Environment: ACC1 
Channel: Telesales + Retail

Steps to reproduce the issue:
 - Enter address: Goethestr. 27 26409 Wittmund Wittmund
 - Select package: "Kabel Internet & Phone"
 - Select tariff: "[3BV:B09] GigaZuhause 250 Kabel, 1.-9. Monat 19,99 €"
 - Select goody on "Gutschriften und Aktionen" section: "[JL5] Gutschrift GigaZuhause Young: 1.-9. Monat: 0 €, 10.-24. Monat: -5 €, danach 0 €"
 - open basket

The prices are not calculated as expected.
As a consequence of the wrong basket also the contract summary is incorrect.

!image-2024-04-10-18-00-56-136.png|width=856,height=463!  

+Pre-Analyses of product configuration team:+
OSF uses the 'Price sliding' field from the Product Catalog to configure the way the price periods are shown in the frontend:

!screenshot-1.png|width=338,height=226!

The numbers in this field are however interpreted as absolute points in time. They should however be interpreted as relative time intervals.

+Concretely this means:+

Price sliding '9:6:' should be interpreted as 0.-9. month, 10.-15. month, 16. month onward.
Currently it is interpreted as 0.-9. month, 0.-6. month, whatever comes afterward.
This obviously does not make any sense, since the second period ends before the first one, so the consequence in the frontend is, that the second period is ignored.

+The obvious fix therefore is:+
The numbers in the "Price sliding" field should always be interpreted as *relative time* intervalls.

 

+Additional proof:+
When checking in the OSF Backoffice for the product properties, the price_sliding of JL5 looks like this:

!image-2024-04-09-15-34-39-869.png!

Looking at this in overview in the frontend, the second time intervall seems to be ignored:

!image-2024-04-10-18-00-56-136.png|width=423,height=229!

Manually changing it to 15 then leads to the following view in OSF:

!image-2024-04-09-15-42-29-039.png|width=737,height=206!

This is, however, still wrong. OSF seems to tread the numbers in the PCAT import as absolute times instead of relative intervals

=> Three sliding prices are in principle possible to show, but the configuration in the product setup is imported and interpreted wrongly

column1: OSF | Wave 8.2 | ACC1 | Status is not getting reflected at order level in omnius.
column41:
We have observed that some orders status is not getting reflected at order level in omnius in ACC1.

In package level it is showing "In-Progress", but in order level its showing "In the first queue".

We have restarted status daemons but issue is still there.

 

Test data: 821283, 821249

 

Push Order request:

<lc:PushOrderStatusRequest
    xmlns="urn:oasis:names:specification:ubl:schema:xsd:CommonBasicComponents-2"

        <lean:MessageSequenceNumber>1777634</lean:MessageSequenceNumber>

|805687|

column259: We are unable to check SKY flow due to this issue.
column504:
Issue was due to resource shortage and when we increased the resources on the nodes the application was able to run as expect.
We Checked the worker nodes and could see that the CPU usage is spiking 100% so we increased the cpu resource on each worker node to 8 cpus.
After increasing resources we can see all new pods are working fine and running. Some pods were stuck in error state, deleted them.

column259: All DSL/FTTH activation flows are impacted due to this issue.
column810:
26/Feb/24 7:02 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;There is a change in SAP Z42 environment where  they have changed the DeliveryServiceId "GLSSTDFCA" to "DHLSTDFCA" where as of now in OGW Drools logic this value is not available.
So OGW needs to add this DeliveryServiceid value in Drools to accept the response from SAP and sent to Omnius.
<DeliveryServiceID>GLSSTDFCA</DeliveryServiceID>
<StandardDeliveryIndicator>true</StandardDeliveryIndicator>
<DeliveryServiceDescription>GLS Standard FN Customer Address</DeliveryServiceDescription>
 
<DeliveryServiceID>DHLSTDFCA</DeliveryServiceID>
<StandardDeliveryIndicator>false</StandardDeliveryIndicator>
<DeliveryServiceDescription>DHL Standard Festnetz Customer Address</DeliveryServiceDescription>

So this is a CR towards Amdocs where this value needs to be updated;;;

1st Fix:
Unklnown “agent_role_UPPER_CASE_ROLEKEY” present.
Additional Foreign key “agent_ibfk_1” was present

COPS_UNITY_TEAMLEADER for ACC2 env.

<Feb 27, 2024 2:05:28,611 PM CET> <Error> <ORACLE.IAM.CONNECTORS.ICFCOMMON.PROV.ICPROVISIONINGMANAGER> <BEA-000000> <oracle.iam.connectors.icfcommon.prov.ICProvisioningManager : removeChildTableValue : Error while updating user

column813:
08/Mar/24 8:42 PM;waseem.akhtar@vodafone.com;RCA:

# Unklnown  “agent_role_UPPER_CASE_ROLEKEY” present.
# Additional Foreign key “agent_ibfk_1” was present on “agent” table linking agent.role_id to agent_role_UPPER_CASE_ROLEKEY.role_id
# This additional foreign key was causing integrity violation when adding permission to agent and failing with 500.

Analysis steps:

# Double checked to confirm this additional table and foreign key ONLY present on ACC1.
# Renamed the table to a different name
# Run resetModules.php
# clear cache
# Check if all modules are updated to latest version. This ensures all application database upgrade scripts are run.
# Table was not created after this on ACC1.
# This confirms the table was NOT created by application.

Resolution steps:

# Delete the Foreign key “agent_ibfk_1” present on “agent” table linking agent.role_id to agent_role_UPPER_CASE_ROLEKEY.role_id
# Unfortunately this deletes a needed foreign key with same name linking agent.role_id to agent_role.role_id
# recreate the Foreign key “agent_ibfk_1” on “agent” table linking agent.role_id to agent_role.role_id



[~taher.golvala@vodafone.com] [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] Issue resolved. Please note this is NOT an application issue. IF possible try to find out who created this table on ACC1.
Thanks to [~sneha.jatti@vodafone.com] for helping with oinvestigation.;;;

column850:
15/May/24 9:53 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,

yes, currently the fix is almost ready after discussions with design team and Ketaki.

in this fix the 24 retry will not be in use anymore, instead the retry will be determined by the ogw_error_handler table.

it will decide how many times to retry, and how much time to wait between the calls.

for this flow the retry will be active for empty response from oneDMS or OGWERR-9900 error code return

for example:
this is a record from the table:

{
    "ERROR_CODE":"OGWERR-9900",
    "ERROR_CATEGORY":"Technical",
    "IGNORE_ERROR_IND":"N",
    "RETRYABLE_IND":"TRUE",
    "MAX_RETRY_TIMES":"3",
    "RETRY_WAIT_TIME":"10",
    "MAX_WAIT_TIME":null,
    "STATUS_TO_SET":null,
    "CHANNEL":"TELESALES",
    "SERVICE_CALL":"ASYNC",
    "SERVICE_NAME":"OneDMS"
}
so the flow will retry 3 times and the wait time will be 10 seconds between every try.;;;

column815:
27/Feb/24 8:48 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Checking with Torsten Brodka on opening SRT for Drools rules change

 

There is a change in SAP Z42 environment where they have changed the DeliveryServiceId "GLSSTDFCA" to "DHLSTDFCA" where as of now in OGW Drools logic this value is not available.
So OGW needs to add this DeliveryServiceid value in Drools to accept the response from SAP and sent to Omnius.
<DeliveryServiceID>GLSSTDFCA</DeliveryServiceID>
<StandardDeliveryIndicator>true</StandardDeliveryIndicator>
<DeliveryServiceDescription>GLS Standard FN Customer Address</DeliveryServiceDescription>

<DeliveryServiceID>DHLSTDFCA</DeliveryServiceID>
<StandardDeliveryIndicator>false</StandardDeliveryIndicator>
<DeliveryServiceDescription>DHL Standard Festnetz Customer Address</DeliveryServiceDescription>

So this is a CR towards Amdocs where this value needs to be updated;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.2 | ACC1 KUD standalone products blocked in checkout after IBAN validation
column41:
Currently KUD TV products for Unitymedia as well as for VKD cannot be booked, as failing in checkout with error message after IBAN Validation.

Steps to reproduce for Telesales channel:

1) Enter unitymedia or VKD adress -> new customer
2) Add KUD product e.g. GigaTV Net, 1.{-}6. Monat 0,{-}€
3) move to checkout, fill in customer details > customer adress in Germany
4) reach to IBAN section, type in GERMAN IBAN e.g. DE20700500000003658888 (Any German IBAN can be taken!)
->IBAN validation is running and successfull
5) Select invoice adress as customer adress and do NOT select any different bank account holder
6) Klick on "weiter" and get error message

_{color:#ff0000}Die ausgewählten kabel-unabhängigen Produkte (z.B. GigaTV App und Net) lassen seit dem 01.04.2018 eine Nutzung innerhalb der gesamten EU zu. Aber nach gesetzlichen Vorgaben nur von Kunden mit festem Wohnsitz in Deutschland.){color}_

_{color:#ff0000}Die Prüfung der Bankverbindung hat ergeben, dass eine ausländische Bankverbindung oder ein abweichender Kontoinhaber angegeben wurden.{color}_

_{color:#ff0000}Leider kann aus diesen Gründen die Prüfung auf festen Wohnsitz in Deutschland nur über den nächsten Vodafone-Shop erfolgen. Bringen Sie hierzu Ihren Personalausweis oder eine Meldebescheinigung mit.{color}_

 

We are not using foreign customer adress or foreign IBAN, and also +*not*+ using foreign invoice adress or different bank account holder
It is not the problem, that its going to be validated if there is any data from foreign countries used! The validation itself is correct process - but the result is wrong! It has to be identified by the system, that this customer is allowed to pay the products so we are able to move to the next section.

 

It seems the booking works sometimes, and sometimes not. Or maybe only for specific constellation of KUD products it works. We need to investigate if there is an issue with the software or not

 

*Positive* examples from this morning:
ID: ** 801847; IAV Weboder ID: 6088191
OSF Order ID: 801861; IAV Weborder ID: 6088197

 

Please note: SAME issue is visible on ACC2, although there is still wave 8.1.5 code present!!

Please check possible side effects from CR780 Change of payment validation check for existing SEPA mandat which was one of the last production fixes and is available on both ACC

column810:
23/Feb/24 1:03 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;SunilkumarCM added a comment -
 
 
Hi [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com]  [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] ,

We have analyzed further and found that there is recent requirement over (https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OAF-690) [!https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/epic.svg!VFDED1FTS-5531: CR780 - Change of payment validation check for existing SEPA mandatIN DESIGN|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED1FTS-5531] which is now available as part of the software where we are testing the above scenario.

As part the requirement we are now showing NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button of payment section if the scenario we are performing meets below conditions.

System will validate if payment method = "direct debit"
 * if yes: system will validate if IBAN = DE-IBAN

 ** if yes: system will validate if bank account owner (payer contact) = legal contact

 *** if yes: the system will validate if the bank account owner address (payer address) = legal address

 **** if yes: the system switches to the next checkout section

 **** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 *** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 ** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 * if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button.;;;

column810: 19/Feb/24 12:25 PM;natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com;Hi [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com], yes it is present with the software which is on ACC1. I just wanted to say with that comment, that the last deployment is not the cause, because it also appeared 3 days before the last deployment;;;
column811:
19/Feb/24 4:46 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;SunilkumarCM added a comment -
 
 
Hi [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com]  ,

I can see for customer you mentioned the PermissionValue is not proper the expected values from Mode 3 response are “Y“ “N“.

If PermissionValue is “Y“ & BEWVersionNumber is equal then BEW is not allowed .

If BEWVersionNumber is greater than stored BEW version number then BEW is not allowed.

In telesales if PermissionID is ADV & Voice log permission not assigned then BEW is not allowed.

 

This is older logic and no changes happened in code. It all depends on Mode 3 response , Stored BEW configuration data & voice permission(In telesales)

Thanks;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.2 | ACC1 | OS-199 | EL discount Summary text and EL discount footnote is missing from contract summary and contract document in Prolongation (VVL) without tariff change scenario
column41:
Hello,

While performing prolongation without tariff change scenario we have observed summary text related to EL discount on contract summary and footnote related to EL discount on contract document is missing.

*Reference story*: OS-36804, OS-5502

Summary text related to EL discount on contract summary should be printed as below:

"Der Mitarbeiter-Rabatt gilt nur wenn und solange ein Nachweis der Zugehörigkeit zum berechtigten Unternehmen vorliegt. Fehlt oder entfällt diese Voraussetzung, gelten ausschließlich die Standardpreise ohne Mitarbeiter-Rabatte."

Footnote  text related to EL discount on contract document should be printed as below

The following footnote #20 shall be printed on the contract: {}Für die Gewährung des Mitarbeiter-Rabatts ist die Vorlage eines gültigen Mitarbeiterausweises, eines Einkommensnachweises der beschäftigenden Firma oder aber ein schriftlicher Nachweis der ,Unternehmenszugehörigkeit erforderlich, der die Zugehörigkeit des für den Rabatt zugelassenen Unternehmens dokumentiert. Liegt innerhalb von 4 Wochen keine Bestätigung vor, gelten nach Ablauf dieser Frist ohne weitere Ankündigung ausschließlich die in der Standard-Preisliste dargestellten Preise ohne die gewährten Mitarbeiter-
Rabatte. Sollte die nachträgliche Prüfung der Mitarbeiter-Legitimation aufgrund der Unternehmenszugehörigkeit eine Zugehörigkeit zu einer anderen Rabattklasse aufzeigen, passen wir den Rabatt auf das für Ihr Unternehmen freigegebene Niveau an. Der Mitarbeiter-Rabatt ist begrenzt auf maximal 4 Karten pro Mitarbeiter. Sollten darüber hinaus Verträge abgeschlossen werden, behalten wir uns vor, den Rabatt bei den überzähligen Karten zu entfernen.Bekommen Sie als Mitarbeiter eines Partner-Unternehmens schon einen Mitarbeiter-Rabatt auf Ihre Mobilfunk-Rechnung und buchen Sie die GigaKombi, erhalten Sie keine GigaKombi-Gutschrift. Alle weiteren GigaKombi-Vorteile bleiben für Sie bestehen.

*Steps to reproduce*:

1. Login to retail portal with PA Agent.
2. Search a Customer (Eligible for VVL)
3. click on Hamburger menu and select an option to search company
4. Verify company search tab is visible(Select tab)
5. Select a Company.
6. Company id and discount level will be stored in session
7. Perform VVL without tariff change
8. Verify based on the selected Company(ID) OSF product configurator should be automatically filter on available products
9. Verify the EL discount level (High or Low), should be available and after selecting it should be added to the shopping cart, when the agent selected the Company ID and desired product
10. Verify Based on the discount level (as a result of the company search) either EL_HIGH or EL_LOW should displayed in the Discounts section of the configurator
11. Verify Discount should be added to the shopping cart and  price should be calculated and shown correctly (in shopping cart and extended shopping cart) based on tariff and discount level
12. fill necesary details.
13. Click on Drucken button to generate contract summary
14. submit order

*Actual Result:* Summary text and footnote text is not getting printed on contract summary and contract document

*Expected Result:* Summary text and footnote text should be  printed on contract summary and contract document
column259: EL discount Summary text and EL discount footnote is missing from contract summary and contract document so customer will not informed about the special conditions that apply to discounts -> only in case of VVL without tariff change

column816:
14/Feb/24 9:45 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Additional info I have received related to this eshop change:

With the upgrade to Tomcat 10, the *default charset* for the request body in eShop REST-API POST or PUT requests *changed from ISO-8859-1 to UTF-8.*

To ensure that REST-API requests will work with eShop release-242.00 and on
 * either include an appropriate "Content-Type" header in the request
 * or use UTF-8 as the character encoding if you do not want to send a "Content-Type" header

We have now done the second change listed here but maybe the other one is also an option;;;

column835:
18/Apr/24 12:36 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;There was a meeting between Kshitij and Andreas with following outcome:
 * Values like "AccountCategory" in Omnius are derived from OGW: Here:- _AccountCategory_ in getCustomerResult for index search and _Region_ in retrieveCustomerInfo mode1 for LegacySearch.
 * As the ADDRESS REGION is in UM Area - it is treated as UM customer, even though he belongs to the VKD Stack

h4. _Possible SD option to be validated/proven:_ 
 * Derive customer stack from GlobalID prefix ("legacy stack")  instead of address region
 * IF improvements required as this is only known by OGW (Omnius can only see LK_ from linked customers) - e.g. introducing new attribute to indicate customers product stack:
 * CustomerSearch()
 * getCustomerDetails()
 * [@Mitra, Gaurab, External Vendor|mailto:gaurab.mitra@amdocs.com]: We should investigate if further interfaces have to be considered (To be discussed on next CR meeting)

[@Kshitij.Srivastava@comviva.com|mailto:kshitij.srivastava@comviva.com]: To check UseCases in Omnius to be considered for an improvement

Further benefit: Omnius Performance increase If product stack information is directly provided by OGW 

 

So team is working on possible solution but will take some time ;;;

Orders should move ahead and reach to backend.

column1: OSF | ACC1 | Wave 8.2 | CR710 | Billing Type is not getting Validated once we reach to Billing address page
column41:
While performing below scenarios 
1) OSF | Wave 8.2 | CR710 |TC_06 Perform X sell on  Cable Customer and add DSL Package on Retail channel with vaild billing address(billing address-complete Address).
2) OSF | Wave 8.2 | CR710 |TC_09_Perform Package Change on Multistack( Cable, DSL and Mobile) customer and check Validate service should be called only once.

In order to verify the Billing address for Cable & DSL stack we performed the flow and observed that Billing type status is not getting changed to validate and stays as Billing

Steps to Reproduce:
1) Login to Telesales/Retail channel as per requirement
2) perform ILS on Cable and DSL
3) change product and move to extended shopping cart
4) Move till Billing Address section and validate in inspect element window 

Actual Result:
Currently Billing type is going as Billing 

Expected Result:
Instead of Type Billing it should change as Validate once billing section page triggers
column259: Billing address is not correctly validating
column504: updated incomment
column810:
31/Jan/24 1:02 PM;silpa.nanda2@vodafone.com;Hi [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] 

Test Data: KD_932340178;;;
column811:
31/Jan/24 7:07 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Charul Gupta added a comment- 
 
 
Checked with Developer @Balaji Ragothaman 
This is not related to CR710, it is already in the code and this Validated tag is trigger based on outcome of validate address client.
It is part of handling in code level, nothing related to functionality differences.

[~taher.golvala@vodafone.com]  please check ;;;
column812:
01/Feb/24 1:15 PM;taher.golvala@vodafone.com;As discussed yesterday its not understandable how we getting the Validated status in some scenarios (i.e. whichever flows we concluded in past) and later in few scenarios where this is not giving the validated status in inspect element.
Also if this case is expected then we need to understand that why in some cases its coming validated and some of them not giving Validated status.

Also if its not related to CR710 we never verified this before in order to compare something in past and present what changes been applied.

So it will be good if we we get the explanation in what cases we get Validated and in what cases we can ignore. ;;;
column813:
06/Feb/24 11:39 AM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Balaji Ragothaman added a comment 
 
Its not related to CR710 based on our analysis. Also its not a defect as its not affecting anything in functionality. in coding level need to understand what implemented in past . 

 

Developer is investigating this issue. 

Thanks 

[~taher.golvala@vodafone.com] [~alka.kshirsagar2@vodafone.com]  fyi ;;;
column814:
07/Feb/24 11:37 AM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;SunilkumarCM added a comment -
 
Hi [~taher.golvala@vodafone.com] 

 

Type value on the xhr request header specifies the type of the address we are validating via the xhr and it is purely for the technical purpose (development purpose to communicate between front end and backend logic before triggering validate service to actual backend). The OSE backend logic will be different which works based on values we send accordingly.

 this is not defect, it purely technical handling, not directly involved in triggering validate address service.

[~alka.kshirsagar2@vodafone.com] fyi;;;
column815:
09/Feb/24 12:34 PM;taher.golvala@vodafone.com;As per the yesterday's discussion with Balaji SunilKumar and vikash from Tech M team. It was mentioned that this is nothing but related to Technical checks and not from testing perspective which we were checking in inspect element mode.
Hence considering that point we can close the defect with no impact on test or respective flow.

cc: [~atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com] , [~gaurav.lanjewar1@vodafone.com]

;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.2 | ACC1 | Offers are landing on the customer details page once edited instead of landing on the checkout page while using UCT link
column41:
We have placed below scenario regarding  -->

TC_49 VKD_Perform ILS saving offer and submitting the same from offer Manager to check UCT_API Flow

*Observation:*

Here we have placed an offer using UCT and send it to back-office agent with Sent to BO status. But, once we edit the offers from offermanager, it doesn't land on the checkout page but its navigated towards the customer details page.
 

 *Steps to re-produce:*
 # Login to Omnius using UCT
 # Select Telesales Agent role
 # Click on Packet andern
 # Proceed to checkout
 # Generate contract
 # Send offer to BO.
 # Login with Back-office agent
 # Retrieve the offer from the Offer Manager page.
 # Observed that offer is not loading correctly (navigating to the customer detail's page)

 

*Actual Result:*

Offer navigated to customer details page

 

*Expected Result:*

Offer should directly land on the checkout page
column259:

column504: change in OGW configuration
column809:
25/Jan/24 5:25 PM;suraj.bhor@vodafone.com;It was disscus on call the below parameter are required to test the epic OS-8566.
There are actually 3 values that need to be set for the dynamic configuration to work:

1)	What is the max number of subscribers of a customer before the popup appears: 
Omnius Backend: subscribers_allowed_in_360 -> set to e.g. “5”
2)	How many subscribers can be selected in the popup: 
Omnius Backend: max_number_of_subscribers -> set below value (1) -> e.g. “4”
3)	From how many subscribers will the mode1 response forward the subscriber count attributes:
OGW property file: <MAX_SUBSCRIBERS_OMNIUS_360> -> set to value (1) -> e.g. “5”
;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.2 | ACC1 | CR752 | Desire Delivery Date values are not getting print in Task Details Section
column41:
While performing the flow for the CR752 it has been observed that Wunschlieferdatum (Desired Delivery Date) value is not getting print in Task Details section.

Order Details : 782101

Steps to Reproduce:
1) Login to Omnius and submit the order
2) Generate Sky ticket
3) Check in SKY Task UI and verify if Wunschlieferdatum (Delivery Date) value is getting reflected under Task Detail section clicking on Task ID


Expected Result:
Generated Wunschlieferdatum Delivery Date value should get generated and reflected under Task details of the Sky ticket

Actual Result:
Currently Wunschlieferdatum is going empty and no value is getting print under Delivery Date Parameter
column259: Delivery Date is not getting reflected in SKY Task details sections if flow is getting failed and Sky ticket been generated

24/Jan/24 3:56 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  I was not creating any order, I am just scanning portal UI tool from time to time to find unidentified issues. And within this quality check I have found tickets with this error message. 

 

After some analysis I have identified, that it seems to be this scenario:

-> Search existing unitymedia customer and perform Move to VKD adress 

 

this is example Order ID from ACC1 - it failed with 2 sky tickets

One ticket because of invalid VPKN (issue is solved, please ignore that) and second sky ticket was for setpermission.


Unfortunately Sky ticket were cleared in between so I am not able to find my two tickets anymore..... But hopefully you can reproduce on your environment for a Move from Unity to VKD.

Seems like in this case the existing customer ID from unity is taken over, instead of recognizing that customer will get a new customer ID from VKD for Move scenario

 

Order ID 782545, Customer ID 1009755201 (initial customer before Move) 

!image-2024-01-24-11-21-17-927.png!

 

Same seems to happen when moving from Unity Cable to DSL product. 

So please check flow Unity Cable to VKD Cable Move, and Unity Cable to DSL Move

 ;;;

Hi [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com]  ,

Further based on investigation above is the expected behavior. Which means for the existing customer we are getting the region value from Install Base and if region value which is from the IB or from the serviceability(in ACQ) is not matching with the below table data which is agreed during the design, then OSE send empty <CustomerList><CustomerDetails>{*}<TargetSystem>{*}.

column259: Delivery option: Delivery to pack station can only be selected via list and not via map
column504:
The Maps JavaScript API team regularly updates the API with new features, bug fixes, and performance improvements. 

As part of this activity some older version of the Maps JavaScript API version are deprecated. Currently its corrected by using version which is available.

Issue might reoccur if Maps JavaScript API deprecate the currently used version 

Solution: New keys have been supplied to T5D for the Map issue with different functionalities per Env. Now the Map is getting displayed for all ACC envs

column1: OSF Wave8.2 | ACC1 | Sky is not sending request to OGW after resuming sky ticket with "Failed-NoResume" from sky tool
column41:

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Submit order.
2. Sky ticket generated.
3. Resume sky ticket with Failed no Resume.
4. Logs (Request) not generated.

Actual: Sky is not sending request to OGW after resuming sky ticket with "Failed" from sky tool.

Expected: Sky should send request to OGW after resuming sky ticket with "Failed" from sky tool.

Test data:

Order id: 780495

column811:
18/Jan/24 4:48 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;This is most likely due to a different behaviour regarding the v2/v3 interface.
For calls to the v2 interface iris has a workaround to determine which CRM the customer belongs to, v3 has no such workaround and the crm must be passed explicitly.

The particular endpoint used by OSF however does not allow passing the crm explicitly, so for the sake of getting the v2/v3 switch I will see if I can port the workaround from v2 to v3.

We might want to then later revisit if the crm parameter can also be passed explicitly by osf.

PR with the workaround: [Pull Request #5895: OS-50918: determine crm based on address. - webgit (kabeldeutschland.de)|https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/FE/repos/ibp/pull-requests/5895/overview];;;

column822:
18/Jan/24 10:36 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;For OSF I would assume that that has to depend on what is selected in the checkout.
For a simple kip order for example you can currently either select to port 1 phone number:
!image-2024-01-18-18-02-24-936.png!

Multiple phone numbers:
!image-2024-01-18-18-02-52-437.png!

Or all phone numbers:
!image-2024-01-18-18-03-27-402.png!

 

What is not clear to me is how the all phone numbers case would be mapped best to the schema.
What does OSF currently send when selecting the all phone numbers option and providing multiple phone numbers?

It seems to me that the case where "Alle Rufnummern" is selected and more than one phone number is provided is not supported by v3. 
I'm not sure why this is a use case in OSF, as "Alle Rufnummern" should not need all phone numbers to be provided by the customer.

Either the OSF interface must limit this case to a single phone number, the v3 interface must be changed, or the mapping just discards all except one phone number.

The best approach I think would be to adapt the OSF interface to match what the api is actually capable of. I'm not sure if something would break with the last option..;;;

column504: backdating has been adjusted in theenv
column809:
03/Jan/24 4:07 PM;thomas.jerke@vodafone.com;This is an backdating issue with the KIAS reference data in your test environment. The campaign socs - e.g. CP2420P23, CPGMS12GB, 12X5SMXS, YOU2SUB19, VFZ_DIS8,PROMSB2GB - have a sale_exp_date of 01.03.2024 in KIAS production ref.-data (reference table SOC). 

By backdating scripts this date is automatically changed to past. Migh be that the backdating period is set too long or the KIAS ref.-data dump is too old. Please check the refernce data setup in KIAS test environment.;;;

column811:
05/Jan/24 5:19 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;Realtime archiving via service API (PPM_658127)  functionality was introduced with OC.157796, but due to multiple issues this was not active until 18th Dec ’23 when latest fix was deployed with OC.000158864 in PR env.
 
By looking at the OA1 logs currently real-time archiving seems to be working fine in PR, as also confirmed by Lac in below mail from DB tables.
 
@Ariadne Thun, Vodafone, Could you please brief the issue you facing due to real-time archiving?
 
@DL_VOIS-VF-DE-AT-TEMS_Team@vodafone.com, 
To de-activate this real-time archiving , we have to set below parameter to false in OM core instances and shut down the OA1(goindr) instance.
File : om-core-env.properties
Parameter: om-core.onedms.archive.active=true
Kindly raise CCR to change the configuration, in case if real time archiving needs to be shut down.
 
CCR - Z_SRT02376962A is raised to make the required changes at PR OM.

Please let us know once changes will be done.
;;;

column1: Z_PRT00133351A | OSF | Wave8.2 | ACC1 | Talend jobs (DWH jobs & Jesi log jobs) are not working for SKY.
column41:
*Talend jobs (DWH jobs & Jesi log jobs) are not working* and hence result in failed state due to hardening of password file name for these Jobs in Talend side. (as per initial investigation) à *Talend jobs are disabled (DWH, Jesi log jobs) in Cron schedule* as of now. So, it will not run again and again.

*PRT Z_PRT00133351A* : OSF : Wave 8.2 : ACC1 : Issue with talend jobs after Wave 8.2 deployment is opened for record purpose.
column259: Talend jobs (DWH jobs & Jesi log jobs) are not working
column504:
Wrong value of the path for the files which contain truststore password and keystore password.
In order to solve that: two new properties were added to sky-config-talend-map.yaml: trustStorePass and keyStorePass to be used by the talend jobs.

column1: OSF | Wave 8.1.5 | ACC1/IT | Create documents in Retail is failing for FTTH DG/DTAG/GPON and DSL for SoHo customers with extended phonebook entry & different billing address
column41:
Getting error after clicking on Create documents button while performing Move Offnet to FTTH DG SoHo customer with different billing address and extended telephone book entry

*Scenario: TC_14_Perform Move Offnet to FTTH DG SoHo customer with different billing address in Retail channel* 

*Error:*
{code:java}
FehlermeldungBeim Erstellen der Dokumente ist ein Fehler aufgetreten. Wenden Sie sich an den Helpdesk.SubmitOrder Service war nicht erfolgreich : An error occurred while processing the message, refer to the details section for more information Message ID: {F8B79EE5-21DF-4640-ABFC-EE5819FE050D} Instance ID: {6BA35E9C-A525-402E-B1A2-23CC31AB29F3} Error Description: There was a failure executing the send pipeline: "Common.Pipelines.SendPipelines.ContextValidatePassThruSendPipeline, Middleware.Framework.Common.Pipelines, Version=1.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=8dd4820aa48e7df7" Source: "XML validator" Send Port: "VFDE_OGW_SubmitOrder" URI: "https://osf-otype1-01-acc1.vodafone.de:8091/VFDESubmitOrderEG/VFDE" Reason: The XML Validator failed to validate. Detail The 'AreaCode' element is invalid - The value '' is invalid according to its datatype 'String' - The actual length is less than the MinLength value.. {code}
 

*Step to reproduce:*
1.Login to Omnius Using Retail channel with Retail FI agent
2.Load existing SoHo cable customer at FTTH DG address and click on Moveoffnet button
3.Configure FTTH DG package with Basis Anschluss and Hardware
4.Keep Home-ID field empty and select Wish-date 
5.Select Building type as apartment building 
6.Select individual connection proof as complete destination phone number
7.Select extended phonebook entry and Select different billing address
8.Select different bank account holder and different delivery address
9.Click on Create documents button
10.Observe error

*Actual Result :* Getting error after clicking on Create documents button in retail channel

*Expected Result :* Order should move ahead without any error

*Test Data :*
Environment: ACC1/IT
FTTH DGW retail order ids:764369 and 764643

*Observations:*
 * *For FTTH DGW telesales, scenario is working fine but with standard phone book* *entry.* 
 * *For FTTH DTAG and GPON in retail channel, we are getting same error.* 

*Test data:*

FTTH DTAG Retail order: 765025

FTTH GPON Retail order: 765105

*Note :* 

1) We have placed FTTH GPON and FTTH DGW retail orders without any error with
*No phone book entry, different billing address, different bank account holder and different delivery address*

Working FTTH GPON Retail Order id :765117
Working FTTH DTAG Retail Order id :765121

2) *Same scenario is working with existing private cable customer*

column1: ON-HOLD | OSF Wave 8.1 | ACC2 |Existing customer scenario with GigaKombi does not work
column41:
Testenvironement: Test1b/ACC2

Testrun: Code Freeze regression testing OSF for PCAT Cable

Description: An existing customer cannot do anything with gigakombimarkers like VB4/VB5/VA1.
Always an errormessage appears in the extended shopping cart (see screenshot) and no further step is possible

Failed testcases:
[https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/SYSSHARQS-1699]

Small description of Teststeps:
Testcustomer: *934829320* (has an old TV product CGT1WG1)
Open OSF ACC2 Telesales
Load Testcustomer
Add a mobile tariff like *[KGM1LH30] GigaMobil L mit PremiumSmartphoneSpecial (Sub 30)*
With hardware "{*}[S00302349] Oppo Find X3 Pro Navy Blue - M{*}"
Go to the existing products of the customer
and click on Paket ändern
TV is opened
Select VB4 as gigakombi - marker
In small shopping cart gigakombi marker appears correctly
in extended shopping cart gigakombi marker appears but error message is thrown (see screenshot)

On ACC1/test3b the same test works correctly
column504: Logic for Gigakombi was changed & there is no GigaKombi available for TV. The markers VB4 + VB5 are not booked anymore. Also for KIP there wsa a change. VA1 was replaced with GKF and GKF is not booked for existing customers. Therefore the defect is not reproducible anymore
column804: As a workaround the agent can trigger execution of the posting rules by selecting and deselecting any product.
column809:
21/Nov/23 6:51 PM;johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com;Analysis results:

To prevent more issues related to [[OTF-902] KIPOPENEDMARKER not being sent in submit order xml || ADD and Drop Cable backend error - Vodafone Global Jira|https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OTF-902] we improved the detection of empty packages in OSF to prevent the agent from entering the checkout with such.

In this case however the package is not empty as it contains VB4. As such our rule should not trigger if the posting rules were executed correctly after clicking the button to create the GigaKombi bundle.

This issue must be fixed by OSF - the posting must be executed after the bundle is created and a product (like VB4) is added to the package.;;;

column831:
13/Dec/23 4:42 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;As explained in the call (and in previous comments on this ticket):
 * the checkout is blocked by a rule that comes from the pcat because the product OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER is not selected.
 * the product is added by the posting rules of the cable rules artifact if there is _any_ change to the TV package
 * after the bundle is created the TV package _is changed as it now contains VB4_
 * as checked in the logs: the posting rules are not called by OSF after the bundle is created

*OSF has to call the posting rules after any change to a cable package, otherwise inconsistencies regarding products/orders/etc are to be expected.* ;;;

Hari Shankar Malviya 
added a comment -
 
Hi Alexander/Simon,
 
 For extended shopping cart min max equal warning rules, there is not relation with cable post rule results or execution.
The rule which is problematic, is a max(0) rule and service to category rule. So if this rule’s service source expression evaluates to true than it will check if cart have max 0 number of products only from the target category. So if product OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER is not part of the package then problematic rule service source expression will evaluate to true and further it will show warning if from target category we have more then 0 products in cart.;;;

14/Dec/23 4:54 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;[~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com], I am not sure if there was any more specific documentation (I will keep searching for a bit), but the following HLD already has a section:
|*Cable artifact rules*
 
The Cable Catalog and PLM colleagues have requested their own rules engine to be applied in the configurator. This is realised with a plugin development where Cable colleagues can upload their Rules Artifact as part of the PLM process. This Rules Artifact consists of the same Sales Rules (in PHP language/cable-speak) that is used currently in ECC front-ends. OMNIUS will share the full-shoppingcart (all packages) to the Rules Artifact, the rules artifact will process ruling, and return the shoppingcart object with modified cable orderlines in Kabel TV, KIP and KUD packages to be displayed in OMNIUS. The Rules Artifact will be called both before a product is selected (on show of configurator, pre-condition) {*}as well as after selecting a product (on adding to the shoppingcart, post-condition){*}. OMNIUS will not be able to have special GUI handling like for internal OMNIUS sales rules when using the Artifact.|

Highlighting added by me.

Full document: [https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/sites/C3-B2B-OneSalesFoundation/IMPLEMENTATION%20Drop1/Deliverables/01%20V-HLD%20Vertical%20HLDs/HLD%202.0/V-HLD_01_Workpackage%201_Scenario%201c-v2%2018.docx]

 

From a slightly newer HLD:
|Apart from the Omnius compatibility rules for cable, specific precondition and postcondition rules from cable are also evaluated within the Cable Rules Artifact. *With each change in the configurator (for cable products) the Omnius rules and Cable rules artifact are evaluated in a loop, until a stable state is reached.* |

Full document: [https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/sites/C3-B2B-OneSalesFoundation/IMPLEMENTATION%20Drop1/Deliverables/02%20FA/FA-01%20Product%20Catalogue/FA-01_30%20HLD%20Wave%203_Product%20Catalogue-v2.11.docx]

column1: OSF Wave 8.1 ACC2 - ON HOLD OSIP-1359 Contract Summary: Price of old TV Product is missing (only OSF)
column41:
test environment: test1b /ACC2 Wave 8.1

Scenario: 
Existing Unitymedia cable customer with following inventory: legacy KIP Product (not Broadvision) and legacy TV Product (Code UMDKLM) orders GigaZuhause 1000 (Broadvision product) - Telesales 

Rabatt UMDTZBK is added --> this is correct / legacy TV product itself stays with "Digitaler Kabelanschluss m. Service)

Fill in all mandatory information in checkout section and move until Contract Summary creation

Contract Summary OSF:
{color:#de350b}Price "Digitaler Kabelanschluss m. Service" 0 Euro --> not ok, Price should be 20,99 Euro{color}

!image-2023-11-08-15-09-20-446.png|width=364,height=318!

If you see the contract summary for same order placed in other portals like ZHP und MHV the behavior and display on Contract Summary is correct (and they also use outputmanagement, so issue has to be on OSF side) :

Price 20,99 is displayed -> ok
!image-2023-11-08-15-10-53-135.png|width=453,height=129!

Test customer was 552907801

order was submitted from ZHP weborder 7836630
column259: Customer is getting wrong price on the contract summary in case of specific TV product constellations -> new change required
column504: No Change Required.
column809:
09/Nov/23 7:56 PM;johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com;From what I can see in VkdGateway the price of the product is correctly returned as:

"nonStandardRate": 17.64, 

which with VAT makes ~20.99€.

The product itself however does not seem to indicate that it has a price nor a non standard rate, both of which should however not be necessary for unity inventory products.

It is noteworthy that the product itself has no price configured in the product setup, maybe the display in the contract summary of OSF does not work if it is an inventory product without a price (and without a non standard rate actually configured in the product setup)?

To me this sounds a) like an OSF issue and b) not like a BV issue.;;;

column1: On-Hold | SPN-OPT-000141353| OSF | Wave 8.1.5 | ACC1 | orders are stuck in initial queue intermittently
column41:
We observed that, intermittent orders are getting stuck at initial queue for all stacks

*Steps to Reproduce:*
 # Login to Omnius with Telesales/ retail channel
 # Configure new activation package
 # Add product in shopping cart.
 # Click on send contract button
 # Submit order

*Actual Result:*

orders are stuck in initial queue 

*Expected Result:*

new activation orders should be move ahead without any error.

*Test data:*

 Order id : 754687

Environment: IT/ACC1

column1: OSF | ACC3 | ON HOLD Wave 8.1 | IMPROVEMENT CR to fix DSL Telesales orders are getting stuck at OnHold-PendingDSLShop
column41:
While performing today sanity we observed that DSL telesales orders are stuck at state OnHold-PendingDSLShop. so that orders are not getting submitted to backend. {color:#de350b}*This is only for ACC3*{color}

*Steps to reproduce:*

Login to Omnius Telesales channel

Select DSL Product

Proceed to checkout

Submit order

Track order in OGW

 

*Expected Result:*

Order confirmation by DSL shop should came from Tivano/Eshop

Order should submit to BE 

 

Test data : 
Order id :  428201  , Barcode : VDE5600000076

Order id : 428193  , Barcode: VDE5600000058
column259: DSL Orders are not getting submitted to backend in case we are changing the sequence on OGW side for OGW order ID
column504: delivery of CR804
column809:
25/Oct/23 12:14 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;Defect to be kept ON-HOLD-- currently here the issue is that OGW is creating a BARCODE which can accept max 8 digits where the new sequence id which is changed for OGW order is is having 9 digits due to which when OGW is trying to search customer is CDM it counts the 8 digits starting from RHS where the last digit is ignored 
So in this case the new order id = 900000073 where while searching it is only calculating 73 ignoring all the 0 digits as they are null.
The last 9 digit =9 is been not counted at all as it only does counting until 8 digits which is 00000073 

To adapt these changes --we need to have a CR in OGW to implement the changes;;;

column1: OSF | ACC2 | Wave 8.1 | Solstice | Existing session is not getting refreshed after submitting the ILS order
column41:
While performing the Solstice ILS and clicking on Vodafone symbol redirected towards configurator and observed that existing session is not getting terminated and seeing the message as below:

*The customer has products created in solstice*
If you want to order new packages for the customer, close this customer, close this customer and create a new package as for a new customer.

Steps to Reproduce:
1) Login To telesales using Solstice Role
2) perform Solstice Search and using existing customer and perform ILS
3) Configure the package and move to extended shopping cart
4) check customer details and move to checkout 
5) create contract summary and submit the order
6) From the submit order page click on Vodafone Symbol on top left corner
7) which will land on configurator page and you will see the message in shopping cart as above.

Expected Result:
Existing session should get terminated once ILS Scenario get submitted and when we directly move to configurator

Actual Result:
In existing ILS solstice flow session is not getting terminated and gets the above error message.

column815:
29/Sep/23 3:00 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;Hi Vikash,
as the logs show the PCAT returns VP0 and 1V1 as visible in this case, so maybe we have a different understanding what "visible" in this case means?
My understanding of visible in this case is:
 * the last call of the cable rules plugin by osf returns a list of packages, each containing a list of products.
 * a product is "visible" for a dropdown if the property "visible" in the last return value of the cable rules plugin for this particular product was "true".

 ** this is especially distinct from the "visibility" of tariffs in the configurator which depends on more information like:
 *** is the product selected
 *** is it configured to be shown in the configurator
 *** is the product "visible" according to the last result of the cable rules plugin

*According to the logs 1V1/VP0 is visible in this case but is never selected by OSF even if the agent selects it in the dropdown*

This is even underlined by the fact that 1V1/VP0 are shown in the dropdown {*}which would not be the case if the were not "visible"{*}.;;;

I do not think it is related to CR676 as it has nothing to do with the json schema, but a change in that CR could of course have impacted OSE to behave differently. According to my knowledge however CR676 only had OGW impact until recently and should have no impact whatsoever on OSE and with which products OSE calls the cable product logic.

column838:
06/Dec/23 8:20 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I further analysed this issue and found the following:

Orders created by OSF contain a field 
{code:json}
"apartmentDetails":{"technicianNeeded":
true/false
}
{code}
As far as I can tell from tests the field is always true if and only if the agent selected the technician_yes option in either the TV or the KIP dropdown during the checkout.

This information should also be passed to the cable rules plugin, in the field `IServiceAddress::technicianNeeded`.

After the selection of technician options in the dropdown the cable posting rules are executed again by OSF, but the the `technicianNeeded` field is not set to true (as it should be if the agent previously selected VP0/TECYESKIP in the technician dropdowns).

This can be checked by searching for `technicianNeeded` in the following log: [^cable_rules_artifact_OS44322_technicianNeeded.log] 
Notice that the last execution contains `TECYESKIP|true`, since the agent selected the kip technician to be necessary.

For fixing this bug the cable rules artifact logs can be used to check if the technician needed flag is passed to the cable rules plugin correctly.
In the meantime we will try to provide a workaround that might resolve most of the issues as well. We have an experimental workaround since version V2330_2024_01_00_032.
Until this issue is fixed on OSF side and we can remove our workaround again I would keep this ticket open however.;;;

column849:
10/Jan/24 9:28 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;[~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] 

Okay, let me go through your message step by step.

For the first test case:
 * I can reproduce it :)
 * I think that only the TV dropdown is shown is correct (according to the up to now still best documentation we have: [Scenario dimension "Technician appointment" - OSF - Vodafone Global Confluence|https://confluence.sp.vodafone.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=103985437]).
 * I think VP0 being selectable is also correct (again according to above documentation, and to some tests we have [Quelle von vkdTechnicianOptions.feature - productSetup - webgit (kabeldeutschland.de)|https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/FE/repos/productsetup/browse/4DevelopmentOnly/tests/unified/features/availability/vkdTechnicianOptions.feature#216-236]).
 * VP0 disappearing afterwards sounds problematic and without investigating I have no idea why it would.
 ** VP0 not being selected anymore however explains that my workaround doesn't work because it relied on the presence of the technician options instead of the flag.

For the second case:
 * I can reproduce the behaviour :)
 * I don't understand the problem with this though? For this particular example you can proceed either with no technician at all (TECNOKIP, TECNOTV are both selectable) or with a technician (TECYESKIP, 1V1 can be selected together).
 * If the issue is the error message, what would be the expected behaviour if a different technician selection would be made by the agent?
 * If the issue is that the TV dropdown is visible at all: that confuses me a bit as well, since our tests would indicate that only the kip options should be shown in this case: [Quelle von vkdTechnicianOptions.feature - productSetup - webgit (kabeldeutschland.de)|https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/FE/repos/productsetup/browse/4DevelopmentOnly/tests/unified/features/availability/vkdTechnicianOptions.feature#239-259]

column809:
27/Sep/23 2:24 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I am not aware of any interface that lets cable control the display of whole dropdown sections. The answer why the whole section is missing can only be given by OSF.

If I had to guess I would assume OSF is hardcoded to check for TECYESKIP, TECNOKIP, UMTECKIP:NOO, UMTECKIP:YES. One of the relevant tests in our test suite is likely:
{code:java}
    Scenario: New cable TV (KAA) and KIP customer without self-install on NE4-VVO address
        Given a KDG service address where "analog and digital" TV is available with object category "NE4-VVO"
        And a KDG service address where internet with data transfer rate "1000" is available
        And self-install is 'not available'
        And a selection
            | productCode |
            | TC2         |
            | 01H:B06     |
        When I get the availability and basket
        Then the products have the states
            | productCode  | state         |
            | TC2          | selected      |
            | 01H:B06      | selected      |
            | TECNOKIP     | not available |
            | TECYESKIP    | not available |
            | TECNOTV      | not available |
            | TECYESTV     | not available |
            | VP0          | selectable    |
            | 1V1          | not available |
            | UMTECKIP:NOO | not available |
            | UMTECKIP:YES | not available | {code}
According to my understanding no kip technician is needed at VVO addresses since the TV technician will handle the installation.
As with the other bug tickets I think we need clarification from business what the expected behaviour is.

column1: OSF | ACC2 | Wave 8.1 | All Stacks | Identisch mit Serviceadresse is not getting removed if we change the address again from same clicking on edit
column41:
While performing solstice flow following below scenario:
TC_12 Perform New Solstice Activation and Validate Delivery Section
But observed with all stacks.

we observed that Identisch mit Serviceadresse is not getting removed if we edit the address again from the same page and use the same address like service address

Steps to Reproduce:
1) Login to Telesales channel using any agent
2) perform serviceavailability and configure solstice package
3) Move to extended shopping and add customer details
4) add same address as service address and move forward
5) On delivery section page check delivery options in drop down
6) there should be 3 options visible as per cable behavior
7) from the same page try changing the address again other than service address clicking on pencil symbol(edit button)
8) which should see the new option out of 3 as "Identisch mit Serviceaddresse" (total 4)
9) again goto edit button in order to edit the customer details page and rechange the address and use the same address like service address
10 ) And check the delivery section details again it should be now 3 options to select, which is not working

Expected Result:
Making changes of address other than service address or same like service should also change the number of options to select in delivery section

Actual Result:
Changing addresses from the same page of delivery section is not also reflecting the number of options to select in delivery section


*Understanding:*
Using Customer address as service address in customer details page should enable below options:
1. Identical to customer address
2. Delivery to different postal address
3. Delivery to DHL Packstation

Using Different customer address other than Service address should enable the below options in delivery section:
1. Identical to service address
2. Identical to customer address
3. Delivery to different postal address
4. Delivery to DHL Packstation

column813:
21/Sep/23 5:30 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;*Guess:* 
Cable product logic tries to rebuild the selection of the agent in each step. This means that certain clickflows are not really supported.

If their are for example two products A and B, A is visible, B is not, selecting A replaces A with B.
If the agent now selects A, A will be added to the selection and the product logic will replace it with B, the agent will see B in the selection.
If the cable product logic is executed again B is not a valid selection because it is not visible.

In this case A would be VP0, and B would be 1V1.

I do not think that there is a simple fix for this issue if my guess is correct.

The two options I see:
 # do not restrict the visibility of VP0 in this case
 ** this would imply that the agent could directly select VP0
 ** since VP0 and 1V1 are mapped to the same dropdown option in OSF -> the agent can only select VP0 together with 1V1, the replacement of 1V1 with VP0 then actually just removes 1V1 since VP0 is already selected.
 # maybe 1V1 should not be selectable in the first place
 ** instead of allowing the agent to select 1V1 which will automatically be replaced with VP0 allow the agent to select VP0 directly instead.

*Open questions:*

Which option is preferred by business?
 * if option 2 is preferred: should this also applied to other portals

What exactly are the affected cases? 
 * likely all test cases where the rule that replaces 1V1 with VP0 applies. 
 * Can business confirm that all cases affected by the rule below should be changed with either option 1 or 2?
 * The rule is: 

{code:java}
Rule 'Replace_1V1_with_VP0_when_ordering_KAI':
When
    selected products contain '1V1' and
    condition 'new_kip_order' applies and
    condition 'digitalSelected' applies
then
    deselect '1V1' and
    select 'VP0' with contract relation set to the main analog product. {code}

According to our investigation we do not have any Compatibility Rules that deselect 1V1, and as said before 1V1 also never appears in the input to the cable rules plugin. 
For completeness we attach the log of the cable rules plugin so you can check for yourself that 1V1 is never passed to the cable product logic as selected: [^cable_rules_artifact372637.log]

Simon;;;

column1: Execution of Defaulted-Obligated rules is not working correctly for mutually-exclusive category
column41:
we are currently struggeling with the following business requirement.

We have a mutually-exclusive category X ( here: access hardware)

 

If any of this Product A of X is chosen than a Product P (here: Product 10004 Shipping_Fee) should be Defaulted.

Only Exception: if Product B of X (here: Eigenhardware) is choosen, than Product P should not be added

 

We build a rule (here: CR006048)

If not B than defaulted-obligated P (Prio 6)
 
First Result:

If we switch from A to B P stay in the cart

 

I added an additional Prio 1 rule: If P is in the cart -> Do not allow P.

 

Result:

If we switch from A to B P is removed, which is fine.

But if I switch back from B to A I get the error

{color:#FF0000}*Die folgenden Produkte: [10004] Versandkosten können nicht hinzugefügt werden weil sie mit der aktuellen Auswahl nicht kombinierbar sind.*{color}

 

+*Expected Result:*+

Product 10004 should be defaulted or removed just by the rule CR006048, no other rule neccessary

 

 

*Steps to reproduce:*

*-ProcessContext ACQ*
 # *Enter any address.*
 #  *Choose any tarif -> A hardware is defaulted*
 # *Switch to hardware Eigenhardware*
 # *Switch back to any other access hardware -> error message is shown*

 

*Details:*

*Defaulted-Obligated - Rule*
{code:java}
<SourceConditions>
    <Aggregator>any</Aggregator>
    <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    <ConditionName>Versandkosten added during ACQ_7994</ConditionName>
    <SourceCondition>
        <Type>cart.containsProductInCategory</Type>
        <Params>
            <Param name="categoryID">FN169</Param>
        </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    </SourceCondition>
    <SourceCondition>
        <Type>cart.containsProduct</Type>
        <Params>
            <Param name="SKU">20099900_sub</Param>
        </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>false</ConditionValue>
    </SourceCondition>
</SourceConditions>
<TargetConditions>
    <TargetAggregator/>
    <ConditionValue/>
    <ConditionName>Product 10004</ConditionName>
    <TargetCondition>
        <Type>Product</Type>
            <Params>
                <Param name="SKU">10004</Param>
            </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    </TargetCondition>
</TargetConditions>
<Operation askconfirmationfirst="false" overrideinitialselectable="false">Defaulted-Obligated</Operation>
<Priority>6</Priority>{code}
 
*NOT-ALLOW-Rule*
{code:java}
<SourceConditions>
    <Aggregator>all</Aggregator>
    <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    <ConditionName>Cart contains Versandkosten 10004_8511</ConditionName>
    <SourceCondition>
        <Type>cart.containsProduct</Type>
        <Params>
            <Param name="SKU">10004</Param>
        </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    </SourceCondition>
</SourceConditions>
<TargetConditions>
    <TargetAggregator/>
    <ConditionValue/>
    <ConditionName>Product 10004</ConditionName>
    <TargetCondition>
        <Type>Product</Type>
        <Params>
            <Param name="SKU">10004</Param>
        </Params>
        <Operator>is</Operator>
        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>
    </TargetCondition>
</TargetConditions>
<Operation askconfirmationfirst="false" overrideinitialselectable="false">Not Allowed</Operation>
<Priority>1</Priority>{code}

30/Oct/23 9:36 PM;marco.abraham01@vodafone.com;I made some further checks on this topic.

First of all we have found a workaround to make this particular business rule working.

However we still have the issue with a defaulted Product P and the check !cart.contains(P)

 

The example here is:

We have a (initial) default rule. If agent selects tariff A default hardware P. Of course this rule is true also in further runs of compRules

Agent switches manually to other hardware Q of this mutually exclusive category

If we have two distinguish rules:
 # cart.containsProduct(P) -> default product X 
 # !cart.containsProduct(P) -> Not ALLOW X 

We get this kind of error message: X cannot be added 

 

Regardless if the first or the second rule gets a higher prio we always run into trouble that either the product is added (but should not) or we get the above error message.

Please explain how to build the rules to make it working the whole time;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.1 | CR716 Futurize regression defect | when booking ES5 on a Selfinstall address where ABK = no, Self install is selected  in the access details for Unity Orders
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (test2b) 

Channel: Retail + Telesales

VKD address: Alte Post 1 44869 Bochum (ABK = no; Selfinstall = yes)

!image-2023-09-06-13-09-31-974.png!

select the Experten-Service Einrichtung for any Broadband Order:

Check the Access details section:

!image-2023-09-06-13-13-05-731.png!

{+}Actual result{+}: when booking Experten-Service Einrichtung on a Selfinstall address where ABK = no, self install  is available in the access details

+Expected result:+ when booking Experten-Service Einrichtung on a Selfinstall address where ABK = no, Technician  should be available in access details

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * create a new customer on a UM address where ABK = no, and Selfinstall = yes, E.G:Alte Post 1 44869 Bochum
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"

 * select any KIP tariff, e. g.: GigaZuhause 100 Kabel, 1.-6. Monat 19,99 €"
 * click on "Optionen"
 * select  {*}Experten-Service Einrichtung{*}" ({+}with this option a technician is booked{+})
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * fill in the customer data
 * click on the button "Weiter"

– > Check which option is selected in Access details

Note:Backend is selecting the technician as expected:

!image-2023-09-06-13-28-30-763.png|width=483,height=125!

OSF:RETAIL:ACC2:Omnius ID:991759

OGW:2695200

CN:1002969303

Unity Backend
column259:
No Business impact because in backend technician is selected.
But confusing for the Agent as in front end it is showing as self install.

column812:
20/Sep/23 4:07 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;This can be changed on cable side, but I am relatively sure that this was never implemented for Unity.

Without CR-716 the agent could select both "Anschluss ist bereits sehbereit" or "Anschluss ist nicht sehbereit" but only "Anschluss ist bereits sehbereit" would actually do anything (selecting a marker product).

With CR-716 only the option with a valid product selection is left, but functionally everything behaves just like before.
The agent basically just had the illusion of a choice before.

If this behaviour should be changed I think it needs to be clarified if there are other cases for unity in which (at a self install address) the option "Anschluss ist nicht sehbereit" should be selectable. The other ES* products come to mind for example.;;;

column1: FTTH DTAG - At a DTAG tariff change from dsl to dtag, the default modem hardware is not deselectable even if it is not defined as DEFAULTED OBLIGATED
column41:
*While change tarif from DSL to Fibre, the preselected modem hardware 20090213 is not be able to deselected (TTWOS Ticket Z_INC02692402A and Z_INC02697357B).*

Expected: The modem hardware 20090213 is not an IAD, it's only an "Hardware Zubehör"/secondary hardware, it should be deselecable, once the customer wanted.

PCAT rule configuration: CR005943 GF Modem defaulted if it is not in installedBase and no FritzBox 5590 existing

<Identifier>CR005943</Identifier>
<PackageType>DSL</PackageType>
<Title>GF Modem defaulted if it is not in installedBase and no FritzBox 5590 existing </Title>

</TargetCondition>

<Priority>4</Priority>
<Channels>
<Channel>*</Channel>
</Channels>
<ProcessContexts>
<ProcessContext>ILSBLU</ProcessContext>

<RuleDescription>OREF-342 Für BK, Glasfaser Modem defaulted, wenn kein GF Modem in installedBase ist und kein Modem integrierte GF Router ausgewählt ist</RuleDescription>
<EffectiveDate>2023-07-27</EffectiveDate>
</CompatibilityRule>
The target 20090213 is defined as DEFAULT, not DEFAULT OBLIGATED.
But even though, the product 20090213 cannot be deselected.
The software team must fix this issue, so the target product 20090213 is going to be put into shopping cart as default, but could be deselected anytime by agent if necessary.

*To reproduce this error:
===============*
Software version: any
PCAT version: see attached file OSF-20230830_wave7_40_FN_2023_08_23.zip
Test stub: see attached file [^FN_ILS_FTTH_DTAG.zip] 
Log file: see attached file [^rules_debug_step3_selectHardware7590.log]

Step on OSF GUI 
============
1. search customer, any string
2. click on "Paket Ändern" change package
3. select a DTAG tarif
4. select any hardware which is not Fritzbox 5590

You would get below window, and the product 20090213 is not deselectable:

column813:
10/Nov/23 12:34 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Hari Shankar Malviya added a comment - 
 
 
Hi [~shuyan.luo@vodafone.com]  ,

Based on the code investigation, it appears that this is not a issue, the manual_override_allowed field value is 0 in the catalog_package_subtypes table which is why its not allowing to deselect the hardware.

When the PCAT files are imported, the values of this field are set according to the values available in the PCAT files, so if the PCAT file does not contain this filed value for any stack, the value is considered to be 0.

When the manual_override_allowed field is set to 1 for a fixed stack, then the hardware can be deselected in the configurator according to the value in the manual_override_allowed field.

!image-2023-11-10-12-33-31-352.png!;;;

28/Mar/24 1:43 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;Rahul Dongre added a comment -



Below is the analysis done by [@Hari Shankar Malviya|mailto:HM00823034@TechMahindra.com] :

 

The functionality working as designed. the code  is intentionally written to remove the deselected product form the cart and  remove all of its associated defaulted products from the cart.

For more information you can go through this function.

removeItemAndParseDefault()

Following are the rules which are evaluated while removing product 20090213_sub from the cart

CR005941: -ACQ
availability.hasHighestPriority(1000000, 'GRUEN', 'FTTH-L2-BSA-DTAG', 'FIBRE', '(ACCESS_SUPPLIER;DTAG)') == true and cart.containsProductInCategory('FN->FN_Package Configuration->Business Configuration->Hardware->Hardware Capability->Access Hardware->FIBRE') == true

Evaluated = True

CR005943: -ILS
cart.containsProduct('FTTH-L2-BSA-DTAG') == true and cart.packageContainsInstalledBaseProduct('20090213_sub') == false and cart.containsProductInCategory('FN->FN_Package Configuration->Business Configuration->Hardware->Hardware Capability->Access Hardware->FIBRE') == true

Evaluated = False;;;

column504: RCA: The issue arises because the exclusive product category that was removed is still stored in the array. Since there are multiple exclusive category products and no conditions were in place to check for the previously removed category product, the loop executed for the removed product as well.

If this rule is evaluating to true, then product must be added to cart.

29/Sep/23 7:38 PM;shuyan.luo@vodafone.com;*Is this a joke, that you guys assigned this ticket to somebody, who is responsible for reference data configuration :-D*

It is many time said, that with the same version OSE and PCAT, different behavior are given on different test servers.
So the reason could be:
- the (standard-)libs which OSE software included, are not in the same version on different server
- the webserver, or the workframes on which OSE are running do not have the same version or same configuration on different test servers ...

There could be many reasons, which could be investigated by software developers or admins for test servers, BUT NEVER somebody, who are delivering reference datas (product catalogues) :-D

So I would assign the ticket back to developer team, they should write down the instructruction or installation guide for the deployment team, so that the admins for test servers could check, which system configuration maybe wrong due the installation/instruction guide.

column1: OSF | Wave 8.1 | CR716 Futurize regression defect | when booking KIP and TV the access details for TV are not displayed
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (test2b) 

Channel: Retail + Telesales

*Please note: there was a change on PCAT side: [[PORPDT-345] BV - Removal of Ready-to-Watch (Sehbereitschaft) Section - DE Jira (vodafone.com)|https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PORPDT-345]*

*When booking first KIP then TV, the expected result should be:*

 # {*}the Access Details for KIP should be displayed but without the technician option{*}{*}{{*}}

 

{+}Actual result{+}: when booking KIP and TV the access details for TV are not displayed

+Expected result:+ when booking KIP and TV the access details for TV should be also displayed

 

!image-2023-07-21-08-34-10-642.png|width=757,height=570!

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * login to ACC2 Retail
 * search for a Cable address, e. g.: Hagelstangestr. 30, 81927 München
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"
 * select any KIP tariff, e. g.: "GigaZuhause 1000 Kabel, 1.-6. Monat 19,99 €"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel TV"
 * select any TV tariff, e. g.: "Vodafone Basic TV Cable inklusive Endgerät (Angebot bei Neubestellung zusammen mit Vodafone TV Connect)"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * enter the customer data and click on the button "Weiter"

– > the access detail for KIP are displayed – > *OK*

– > the access detail for TV are NOT displayed – > *NOT OK*

21/Sep/23 4:32 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;In order to properly fix this I assume that cable and OSF will have to deliver a fix.

According to the answer from [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-42115?focusedId=2910953&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-2910953 the display of the tv access details depends on the availability of the products TECNOTV and TECYESTV reported by the cable logic.

*Why does the workaround work?*

My *assumption* is that OSF remembers the availability of TECNOTV and/or TECYESTV from a previous execution of the cable logic.

If KIP is selected first, then the first executions of the cable product logic will return TECNOTV and TECYESTV as not available. 

If TV is selected first, then the first executions of the cable product logic will return either TECNOTV and/or TECYESTV as available.

-> This is something that has to be fixed by OSF

{*}What is the implication of the Workaround?{*}{*}{{*}}

Assuming cable product logic would return TECNOTV or TECYESTV as bookable the issue might persist in OSF, since as long as KIP is selected first TECNOTV and TECYESTV will still not be available from the start.

*Open questions from my perspective:*
 * which products exactly control the display of the tv access details in OSF?
 ** Is it only TECYESTV and TECNOTV or also products like VP0, 1V1?
 ** Is this controlled by special tags on products or categories, or are the products hardcoded in OSF?
Maybe [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] can answer this question?
 *  in which scenarios should which technician option be bookable in OSF?

 * 
 ** we have a list of ~80 test cases. Some of these are apparently not correct.

13/Jun/24 2:32 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;Hi all,
so, PORPDT-345 will not make this requirement obsolete, it will just slightly shift how it looks.

The new requirements are: if only TV is ordered, show the section. If TV + Internet is ordered, don't show it.

The new problem is this:
If the agent books the packages in the following order
 * TV
 * KIP

then the TV accessibility section is shown, but it should not.

The problem is still the same as described by [~simon.auch@vodafone.com] in the comment from 21/Sep/2023: 
OSF seems only to decide on whether to show the accessibility section for TV when the TV package is opened. So,
 * we first open TV and book a TV Connect ---> OSF sees that 1V1 and TECNOTV are available and correctly assumes that it should show the TV accessibility section
 * we then open the internet section and book some GigaZuhause tariff ---> from now on, 1V1 and TECNOTV are not available anymore, but OSF seems to not update its opinion on the TV accessibility and will display it anyway
 * IF the user just simply opens the TV package again (without changing anything), OSF updates again and will correctly NOT display it

This is something we cannot fix and still need a change from OSF.;;;

column849:
01/Jul/24 7:38 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;[~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] 
Thank you for the re-test.

The failure in case 2, where the technician option for KIP is wrongly displayed, is again the OSF bug discussed further below:
- when you book KIP first, then OSF calculates the technician option it wants to show for KIP, which is for a pure KIP order on an self-install address currently "Anschluss ist sehbereit".

- when you then book TV, it will not update the technician option it wants to show for KIP, and just show it regardless.

- when you just simply open the KIP package after the TV selection again, OSF _will_ update its opinion and not show the KIP technician section.

We cannot do anything here on our side and would need a fix from TechM side, so that OSF will always update both the TV and KIP technician section, no matter which package is currently opened.

 

About the "Verbindungsdaten speichern" field I don't know much unfortunately --neither how it is controlled nor what the desired logic behind it is.;;;
column851:
02/Jul/24 3:06 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;Hi, Ariadne,

{*}{color:#de350b}yes, I can confirm that in any case where we book KIP + TV (no matter if Broadvision or not, no matter which order we book it in), no technician section should be shown{color}{*}. 

The reason why this fails is as I tried to point out in my comment below. It really is pretty confusing, I apologize for that. I had a call with Natasa where I explained the problem, because it really is a bit hard to grasp.

So again in case of Broadvision what happens is:
 - [In the KIP package] KIP is booked, TV Connect is added because of Broadvision ---> OSF understands that no section for KIP should be shown because KIP + TV is booked and remembers that

 - [In the TV package] TV Digital is booked ---> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked

==> no KIP or TV technician section is shown

In case of Not-Broadvision:
 - [In the KIP package] Only KIP is booked, but not TV yet ----> OSF supposes that a technician section should be shown for KIP (because only KIP is booked) and remembers that
 - [In the TV package] TV Digital + TV Connect is booked ----> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked, but doesn't update the reasoning for KIP

==> technician section is shown for KIP, but not for TV;;;

column842:

maybe it was not clear what I meant with "All information until now seems to conflict with the unity case":
 * We have multiple answers (in this ticket and in other tickets) saying that TECNOTV and TECYESTV control the display of the section (and did so in the past)

 * 
 ** this can't be the case for unity as those are not aligned products
 * In other answers it was mentioned that it is controlled not by TECNOTV and TECYESTV but by categories containing TECNOTV, TECYESTV, 1V1, VP0
 ** sound better, but also all of these products are not aligned and should never have been orderable for unity

In the newly encountered behaviour by Devi (https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-42066?focusedId=2974883&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-2974883) suddenly the access details are shown. Someone has to look into the OSE source code and check _systematically_ when this section is shown. I expect there to be _something_ hardcoded for VFW, but I cannot check that myself.

Without an explanation from OSE side when this section is shown I don't know how else to help with this defect. If it is supposed to be based on the orderability of specific categories {_}then the new behaviour is a OSE contradicts it because no product from that category is orderable in the scenario clicked by me{_}. So for starters this could be analysed and maybe we get some insight which logic we are missing from OSE.  

I would not open another defect for this observation.;;;
