column1: OSF | Wave 8.2 | ACC3 | Unable to perform pares processing for retail orders in ACC environment.
column41:

Contract document's session is processed successfully but pares processing of contract summary  is failed with below error.

We are unable to perform pares processing in ACC3 environment.

In Pares there is no connectivity to ACC3 environment and hence session wont able to process.

We tried one session and we are getting error as below

column1: OSF | ACC1 | In Cable address new acquisition of KUD standalone via telesales is blocked as IBAN validation is not working as expected
column41:
In unity address new acquisition of KUD standalone via telesales is blocked.

*Steps to recreate:*

1)Place a new order in Telesales in NRW or KBW region.
2) Select a KUD Standalone product
3) Fill all the necessary details in the checkout region.

{*}In Billing section, click card symbol Enter Bank account number and sort code{*}, IBAN validation is OK, SEPA is OK
4) Try to complete the order -> but error message says its foreign bank account which is not the case
column135: 07/Jun/23 12:57 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;IBAN validation not working with bank code and sort code.docx;https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/secure/attachment/1073116/IBAN+validation+not+working+with+bank+code+and+sort+code.docx
column259: Its not possible to book KUD products for both VKD and Unity in case IBAN validation is not working as expected -> copy & pase in of IBAN should help
column504:
When we click on creditcard symbol on the right and  enter details like bank account number , it automatically creates IBAN and prefills it.
In this particular scenerio, logic to identify IBAN country check was not working because in this case IBAN is prefilling through creditcard symbol automatically.
So enhanced the logic to identify if the prefilled IBAN is germen IBAN or no so that residencecheck behaviour can be accordingly handled.

 This should happen with an valid german IBAN as well, but it is not clear why this was implemented like this and if there was a communication issue or not . If there was, we need clear specifications on how this should work exactly and the different cases so we can implement an appropriate fix.

Alexandra Vaduva added a comment -
 
 
Hi Harsha/Ari,

This was clear from the beginning, yes, but as I mentioned, the implementation was intended to be like this :

*In case of telesales, if sepa is true, then this check will be shown and the flow is blocked → agent is not able to continue*

Which means that it does *NOT* matter _what IBAN is used_ , this will be shown if the sepa is true and *If the KUD product is part of cable_app_de category .* 

I agree that the way this is working is not consistent : in one case the agent is able to continue but in another the agent is not able to continue.

The final question is - when should the agent be able to continue the checkout process and when should the agent be blocked? According to the initial documentation the agent should not be able to continue and according to these comments the agent should be able to continue .

What is the purpose of this error message and what was wrongly implemented exactly? We can implement a fix according to these comments but we need to know if the issue is that the whole implementation was not done correctly or not, in order to fix the actual issue and not just a particular case .;;;

Hi [~devi.jampana@vodafone.com]

We have analyzed further and found that there is recent requirement over (https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OAF-690) [!https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/epic.svg!VFDED1FTS-5531: CR780 - Change of payment validation check for existing SEPA mandatIN DESIGN|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED1FTS-5531] which is now available as part of the software where we are testing the above scenario.

As part the requirement we are now showing NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button of payment section if the scenario we are performing meets below conditions.

System will validate if payment method = "direct debit"
 * if yes: system will validate if IBAN = DE-IBAN

 ** if yes: system will validate if bank account owner (payer contact) = legal contact

 *** if yes: the system will validate if the bank account owner address (payer address) = legal address

 **** if yes: the system switches to the next checkout section

 **** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 *** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 ** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 * if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button.

please check after [OS-52308] OSF | Wave 8.2 | ACC1 KUD standalone products blocked in checkout after IBAN validation - Vodafone Global Jira resolved ;;;

column1: NEW CR: CR755 | OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | End price of Hardware is not correctly pass to VORAS because of incorrect HWBaseNetPrice and HWBaseGrossPrice in Submit order request for Mobile SOHO Business orders.
column41:
We have performed Mobile SOHO Business New Activation order in Retail channel, In this scenario, VORAS Team observed that Incorrect end price has been delivered to VORAS from Omnius because of incorrect HWBaseNetPrice and HWBaseGrossPrice in Submit order request.

 

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
 # Create Mobile SOHO Business RV Package.
 # Proceed to checkout and submit order.
 # Verify SubmitOrderRequest for HWBaseNetPrice and HWBaseGrossPrice.

Test details:

Omnius Order id: 700815
Omnius Order id: 782001
Actual: End price of Hardware is not correct because of incorrect HWBaseNetPrice and HWBaseGrossPrice in Submit order request.

 

Expected: Correct HWBaseNetPrice and HWBaseGrossPrice generate in Submit order request to calculate correct value for Endpoint.

 # If IBAN =German means starts with prefix “DE” then system must by default enable BIC input field as mandatory input and system must allow to continue the sales flow when agent captures the BIC.
 # If IBAN is non German means not starts with prefix “DE” then system by default enable BIC input field and system must allow to continue the sales flow when agent captures the BIC(BAU).

For German IBANs the BIC validation (with OTF-724) should work like for non German IBANs (AS IS). Here Omnius validates BIC without calling IBAN service.

column1: ON HOLD OSF | Wave 8.0 | ACC1 | OTF-774 | IBAN format is not validated when service "ConvertAndValidateIBAN" fails
column41:
Browser: Chrome
Environment: ACC1

Channel: Telesales + Retail

Test address: Von-Galen-Str. 63, 51063 Köln

 

{+}Actual result{+}: IBAN format is not validated

 

{+}Expected result{+}: IBAN format should be validated

 

+Steps to reproduce:+

 
 * deactivate the service "ConvertAndValidateIBAN" in OIL
 * load any address on ACC1, e. g.:  "Von-Galen-Str. 63, 51063 Köln"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel TV"
 * select any TV product
 * continue with the order until the Payment Details
 * enter an IBAN with invalid format, e. g.: "1"
 * enter a BIC with invalid format, e. g.: "1"

– > error message is displayed for the BIC, that the format is not correct – > *OK*

– > for the IBAN no error message is displayed – > *NOT OK*

*!image-2023-05-13-08-32-50-613.png!*

column811:
12/May/23 2:59 PM;bhavesh.renpara1@vodafone.com;Hi,

Ideally permanent account number only can be reflected in Omnius if OGW sends to us.

*I1010 - UpdateTemporaryCustomerID:​*
# This service pushes permanent customer ID from OGW to OSE.​
# OGW pushes message to amdocs.ogw.customerupdate queue.​
# I1010 service pulls message from this queue and puts in dyna.ose.setstatus queue.​
# status daemon pulls message from dyna.ose.setstatus queue and updates in table “catalog_package”->parent_account_number

So check and share the below logs to check if first OGW has sent permanent account number.
- OIL archive logs for service I1010. For the day when the permanent account number was pushed by OGW. 
- Status daemons logs to check further if received account number was  update.

[~bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com] As far as i know process(mentioned above) for updating permanent account number at our end should same for Unity media as well. But you can double check with our BA.

Regards,
Bhavesh Renpara;;;

column817:
18/Jan/23 8:21 PM;sukhdev.singh@vodafone.com;Hi [~arian.ghallaj@vodafone.com] ,

 

Please see the mail response from YairAharon on the same:

"Just to make the example of CUSTOMERID to be clear. Let’s use the following UM (test) data: legacy Customer-ID as 109235205 from the NRW region.

Based on the mapping defined in the confluence page, the CUSTOMERID is formatted as CUMST.UMREGION (region decode: 1= NRW ; 2= HSN ; 3= KBW) + CUMST.CUCNO (legacy Customer-ID).

So the CUSTOMERID identifier in MRT will have the value: {*}{color:#FF0000}1{color}{*}109235205 ."

[^FW_ MRT- UM identifiers.msg]

You need to add region code before the UM Customer Id.

[https://apigee-xtest03.rat-hub.citt.connect-vf.de/masterRoutingTable/v1/routing//{*}{color:#FF0000}1{color}{*}1003458101?id_type=CUSTOMERID|https://apigee-xtest03.rat-hub.citt.connect-vf.de/masterRoutingTable/v1/routing//1003458101?id_type=CUSTOMERID&market=NRW]

market is optional parameter.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave7.1 | ACC1&ACC2 | Telesales | Unitymedia orders with manual approval do not reach status completed
column41:
In case unitymedia order is not approved automatically in RNS, we are missing the order status and customer number in OSF.

Steps:
 * start order for unitymedia in Telesales (e.g. with KIP)
 * Submit order and check weborder ID in IAV
 * Identify reference ID is created in unity backend but order is not approved automatically
 * Approve order with the given reference ID in unitymedia backend (No new order is created! Weborder ID is set as external reference)
 * Check status / customer number in VKD and OGW -> information for customer ID is missing and status is not completed

Expected:

Also for manual approved orders the status is set to completed and customer ID is transferred via VKD to OSF

07/Dec/23 1:51 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;Updates:

 

OGW needs the customer number in case Unity Manual Approval Orders in Telesales and Retails, which should be provided from VKD to OGW within the existing FulfillmentStarted Request.

 

The customer number is atm provided only for Auto Approval Orders, but missing for Manual Approval orders, therefore the document cannot be archived and the OGW processing remain in status pending (the VKD status is SUCCESS but the orders don't get Sucecss status in OSF Fronend):

An error was encountered while invoking ScanView-SaveDocument WS. Details [Error_Code: HTTPOutbound_0001, Error_Message: Received a fault from processing server for service '/ScanView-001/SaveDocument': An invalid number format or number value was encountered.

Note: Retail Manual Approval Orders don't have this issue because the call to oneDMS/Customernumber is not needed for the E2E flow. They get the Status Success.

 

As the customer number has not been sent for Manual Approval Order until now, a new PST change is required.

I will take the topic with me and check if we can request this change at the PST CAT train, Team Ash(Benjamin Sachse) or Nora.

 * no difference between retail and telesales from cable perspective
 * example set status messages received by OSF
 * fulfilment started from manual approval
